Description: Gmail is an email service developed for limited release in 2004 and fully launched in 2009 by Google.

Outlook.com is an email service connected to a web-based suite of contacts, tasks, and calendaring services. It was founded in 1996 as Hotmail, re-launched as MSN Hotmail after Microsoft acquired it in 1997, later rebranded to Windows Live Hotmail, then re-launched as Outlook.com in 2013.
Yahoo Mail is a web-based email service operated by Oath.
Daum Mail is the main email service of Kakao, a South Korean internet company established in 2014 following the merger of Daum Communications and Kakao.
Yandex.Mail is an email service offered by the Russian company Yandex N.V.
Mail.Ru is an email service started in 1998 by the Russian internet company Mail.Ru Group Limited.
